Chess legend Bobby Fischer, facing prison in the US, seeks Icelandic citizenship to avoid deportation from Japan.
Despite being engaged to the head of the Japan Chess Association, Fischer's US nationality complicates his case.
Iceland's parliament granted him citizenship, potentially resolving the standoff.
Fischer, critical of the US government, renounced his US citizenship and desires German nationality.
Japanese officials await confirmation of his release with Icelandic citizenship.
Supporters anticipate his relocation to Iceland, where he is hailed as a hero.
The vote for Icelandic citizenship paves the way for Fischer's release from Japanese detention, ending his legal uncertainty.
